The --start-device-id can be any vertex within the graph including subnet CIDR addresses.
[EXAMPLES]
.PP
\fBnmdb-graph-network -L3 --start-device-id Internet | dot -Tpng -o layer3.png\fR
.PP
\fBnmdb-graph-network -L2 --start-device-id Internet | dot -Tpdf -o layer2.pdf\fR
.PP
\fBnmdb-graph-network -L3 --start-device-id 192.168.1.1/24 | dot -Tpdf -o layer3.pdf\fR
